STRINGS
->Indexing & Slicing methods
->string is a sequence of characters inside quotes (' ' or " ")
ex:- name = "Python"
     greeting = 'Hello'
->String Indexing - Each character in a string has a position (index). Indexing starts from 0.
ex: word = "Car"
    print(word[0])
o/p:- C
->String Slicing - You can extract parts of a string using [start:end], where start in cluded and end is excluded.
ex:- word = "Car"
     print(word[0:2]
o/p:- Ca
->Strings come with helpful built-in functions like 
text = "hello world"
print(text.upper())     # HELLO WORLD
print(text.lower())     # hello world
print(text.title())     # Hello World
print(text.replace("world", "Python"))  # hello Python
print(len(text))        # 11 (length of string)
->Negative Indexing: strings indexed from the end using -ve numbers
ex:- word = c a r
    index = 0 1 2
    -ve = -3 -2 -1
word[-2:] => starts at -2 i.e., ar
***Practise***
1)Store your name in a variable. Print;The first letter,The last letter,The middle part (slice)
name = "Shravya"
print("First letter:", name[0])       => S
print("Last letter:", name[-1])       => a
print("Middle part:", name[1:5])      => hrav
2)Ask the user for a sentence. Print the same sentence in:UPPERCASE,lowercase,Title Case
sentence = input("Enter a sentence: ")
print("Uppercase:", sentence.upper()) => BVRIT HYDERABAD
print("Lowercase:", sentence.lower()) => bvrit hyderabad
print("Title Case:", sentence.title()) => Bvrit Hyderabad
